summary: This document is a warranty deed executed on August 13, 1961, transferring property located on Little St. James Island in the U.S. Virgin Islands from a group of individuals to Arch W. Cummin. The deed outlines the terms of the sale, including the purchase price of $470,000 and the rights and responsibilities of both parties involved.
